Ryukyuan languages
"The Rykyan languages (Okinawan: , ""Ruuchuuguchi"") are a group of Japonic languages spoken in the Ryky Islands, the southernmost part of Japan. The languages are Amami, Kunigami, Okinawan, Miyako, Yaeyama and Yonaguni."
"Although Japan says the Ryukyuan languages are dialects of Japanese, most linguists see them as languages. This is because Japanese speakers would not be able to understand Ryukyuan without learning it."
